Senior Leandro Suarez scored two goals and added an assist as the Dover boys soccer team defeated Morris Catholic, 5-1. Senior Juan Osorio and sophomore Sebastian also scored one goal each. With the win, Dover improved to 10-1 on the season. 
Jefferson 1, Hackettstown 0: Senior Oscar Aguilar scored the lone goal of the game to lead Jefferson (6-4-1). 
High Point 0, Lenape Valley 0: Garret Potter made 10 saves for High Point, and Matt Ellingworth made four saves for Lenape Valley in the draw. 
GIRLS SOCCER 
Butler 7, St. Elizabeth 1: Seven different Bulldogs scored in the win. Bella Ferriso scored the lone goal for St. Elizabeth. 
Kittatinny 3, North Warren 2: Senior Gabby Sarni scored two goals and senior Delaney Koch added another to lead Kittatinny (6-6). 
Jefferson 4, Hackettstown 0: Morgan Carline, Amber Loomis, Ashley Hutchinson and Mackenzie Barkley all scored one goal each. Megan Smith made two saves to earn the shutout. 
High Point 2, Lenape Valley 0: Freshman Jackie Harnett scored both goals for the Wildcats. 
FIELD HOCKEY 
Morristown 1, Sparta 0: Olivia Graham scored the game-winning goal in overtime. 
Oak Knoll 4, Madison 1: Stephanie Dellavia scored the lone goal for the Dodgers in the loss. 
Newton 1, North Warren 0: Natalie Rivas scored the only goal of the game. Amanda Alessandra made one save in the shutout victory. 
TENNIS 
Morristown-Beard 5, Hanover Park 0: Singles: DeeDee Passione (MB) def. Monica Chen 6-1, 6-0; Madeline Sit (MB) def. Maria Ramos 6-2, 6-3; Grace Kellogg (MB) def. Sabrina Asral 6-0, 6-0. Doubles: Tori Krouse and Paige Williams (MB) def. Krupal Ray and Eileen Foerster 6-2, 4-1; Olivia Land and Blake Kernen (MB) def. Miranda Asral and Genna Dominguez 6-1, 6-1. 
Mountain Lakes 5, Cresskill: Singles: Emily Krupnick (ML) def. Lauren Stark 6-0, 6-0; Kim Yi (ML) def. Kamilla Azbel 6-2, 6-0; Sanjana Ratakonda (ML) def. Sophia Kolodzinski 6-3, 7-5. Doubles: Melissa Mao and Allie Gregorek (ML) def. Sophie Cho and Michelle Yu 6-2, 6-0; Anastasia Zorlas and Grace Chuan (ML) def. Pooja Balar and Olivia Newman 6-1, 6-1.
